modules.name: Control.Comonad.Cofree.Trans
modules.comments:
This module defines a lazy implementation of the _cofree monad transformer_.
Given a `CofreeT` f m a:
- 'f' is a `Functor`, generally representing an AST,
- 'm' is a 'Monad', generally representing an effect,
- and 'a' is the type of the annotation.

Usually, you would use `CofreeT` to annotate an existing AST with
metadata such as source locations, file names, etc.

declarations.comments: The cofree comonad transformer for the functor 'f'.
declarations.title: CofreeT

declarations.comments: Construct a `CofreeT` from a lazy computation with an annotation 'a'.
declarations.title: cofreeT

declarations.comments: Construct a `CofreeT` from a computation with an annotation 'a'.
declarations.title: cofreeT'

declarations.comments: Obtain the annotation stored within a `CofreeT`.
declarations.title: head

declarations.comments: Obtain the inner computation stored within a `CofreeT`.
declarations.title: tail

declarations.comments: 'hoist' the effect type using a natural transform.
declarations.title: hoistCofreeT

declarations.comments: 'interpret' the inner functor using a natural transform.
declarations.title: interpretCofreeT

declarations.comments: Both 'interpret' and 'hoist' the inner functor as well as the effect using natural transforms.
declarations.title: bimapCofreeT

modules.name: Control.Monad.Free.Trans
modules.comments: This module defines a stack-safe implementation of the _free monad transformer_.

declarations.comments: The free monad transformer for the functor `f`.
declarations.title: FreeT

declarations.comments: Lift an action from the functor `f` to a `FreeT` action.
declarations.title: liftFreeT

declarations.comments: Change the underlying `Monad` for a `FreeT` action.
declarations.title: hoistFreeT

declarations.comments: Change the base functor `f` for a `FreeT` action.
declarations.title: interpret

declarations.comments: Change the base functor `f` and the underlying `Monad` for a `FreeT` action.
declarations.title: bimapFreeT

declarations.comments:
Like `runFreeT`, but for running into some other FreeT without the
overhead that `MonadRec` incurs.
declarations.title: substFreeT

declarations.comments: Unpack `FreeT`, exposing the first step of the computation.
declarations.title: resume
